a.xlink:title: A group of attributes that are applicable to objects, to be used when defining a complex type that is an extension of a simple type.

An upper value in nanometers for the lighting spectrum used in capturing an iris image
An X coordinate of a facial feature point
A Y coordinate of a facial feature point
A number representing the distribution of the parameter over thousands of fingerprints approximating a Gaussian distribution.
A pitch uncertainty
A roll uncertainty
A yaw uncertainty
A feature's X coordinate
A radius of position uncertainty (PUM) in the manual or automatic placement of the core in integer units of 10 micrometers
A feature's Y coordinate

A number indicating the number of bits that are data stored in every second of an audio file.
A number of distinct channels or output devices that can be used to disperse the audio.
A number of samples per second taken from a continuous signal to make a discrete signal.
A number of cases contained in a CaseSet , or otherwise related to a Case.

A number identifying the position of the conveyee if there is more than one associated with the same conveyor during the same period of time. For example, for a truck consisting of a tractor with two trailers, the first trailer would have a sequence number of one.
A number of files in a file set.
A value indicating the size of a data file.
A resolution at which an image is captured. Units are pixels per inch.
A multimedia file size in kilobytes (kB).
a data rate is the rate at which information being transferred. It is expressed in terms of [amount of information] per [unit of time].

A total number of removals from foster home to date.

A number of days a person is credited with spending in confinement.
